rent genres and fan bases in order to make sense of our recent past and give new insights into the decade that defined both globalisation and excess. Packed with archival and cultural research but written with verve and spark, the book offers as much to general readers as to scholars of this period, presenting a distinctive and definitive contemporary history of 1980s Britain, from pop to politics, to cold war cultures, censorship and sexuality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNineteen eighties. 0aPopular culturezGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a1980s.  aCold War cultures.  acontemporary history.  adisasters.  agender and sexuality.  ahistory of television.  alists.  apolicing.  apop and politics.  apress control and censorship.1 aRobinson, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616727940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526167279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526167279/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles